From b5afe7afa4d58cfab8bce890e4dece131ad33779 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 28 May 2026 14:30:21 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(solvers): default BestPulseCallback + JLD2 auto-save in
 solve!
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

solve! now installs a solver-agnostic BestPulseCallback by default
(both Ipopt and MadNLP) that records the iterate with the smallest
objective value whose primal infeasibility falls under
inf_pr_threshold. A CompositeIntermediateCallback composes the tracker
with any user-supplied AbstractIntermediateCallback.

After the solve, the final trajectory (plus the tracked best-so-far
snapshot, if any) is dumped to JLD2. The default landing site is
/tmp/pulse_<random>.jld2 — overridable via the save_path kwarg, or
disable via save_solution=false.

AbstractIntermediateCallback signature now accepts obj_value, inf_pr
and a trailing kwargs... so backends can forward more solver state.
The Ipopt adapter feeds the full IpoptOptimizerState through; the
MadNLP adapter reads solver.obj_val / solver.inf_pr defensively.

